products.description: Cisco Cloud Management is a Cisco Secure Client module that enables cloud-driven profile and software updates. It also lets the endpoint use Cisco Secure Client Cloud Management infrastructure to manage deployments.
Cisco Secure Endpoint is an Endpoint Detection & Response (EDR) module that integrates prevention, detection, threat hunting, and response capabilities.

[Recommended for Cisco XDR] Cisco Endpoint Visibility Module (EVM) provides enhanced endpoint telemetry capture for enriched threat context and enhanced correlated detection in Cisco XDR. EVM is designed to co-exist with and complement an existing Cisco or 3rd-party endpoint security deployment with endpoint telemetry.
Cisco AnyConnect VPN provides secure remote access VPN (RA VPN) functions for your endpoints. This module also includes core functions required by other Secure Client features.
Cisco Umbrella provides cloud-driven security when accessing Internet resources.
Cisco Diagnostics and Reporting Tool collects data for troubleshooting Cisco Secure Client.
Remote Access VPN (RA VPN) - Supports remote access VPN connectivity prior to Windows login.
Endpoint health check - System scan (posture) for Cisco Identity Services Engine (ISE).
Endpoint health check - System scan (posture) for remote access VPN (RA VPN).
Cisco Network Access Manager is an alternate Windows networking supplicant that includes capabilities not offered by the built-in OS functions.

products.description: [Recommended for Cisco XDR] Cisco Network Visibility Module provides visibility into network-connected devices and user behaviors.

Installs the Cisco Secure Access Root Certificate into the host computer's certificate store. A Certificate Authority (CA) signed root certificate is required where Cisco Secure Access must proxy and decrypt HTTPS traffic that requests a web resource.
Cisco Zero Trust Access provides secure access to remote private resources. This capability is used in conjunction with Cisco Secure Access.

Orbital provides endpoint visibility and control. It allows you to run queries and scripts to investigate and respond to threats. Note: Secure Endpoint customers should not enable this module. Deploy Orbital through your Secure Endpoint policies under Advanced Settings -> Orbital

[Recommended for Cisco XDR] Cisco Forensics Module provides digital forensics and incident response (DFIR) capabilities to Cisco XDR. It includes a remote endpoint interactive response shell, forensic acquisition, and reporting. Requires Cisco XDR or Breach Protection Suite Advantage and higher.
